<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="543" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,294,643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[151,388,294,318]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Schmidtea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="polychroa">
<emphasis box="[151,388,294,318]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Schmidtea polychroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed mainly in the northern part of the island in large hydrographic basins as well as small rivers (
<figureCitation box="[299,368,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1573,1595]" captionTargetBox="[479,1117,369,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[399,1187,287,1551]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Geographic distribution of species of the genus Schmidtea and Girardia recorded from Sardinia. 1, Rio Fiume Santo; 2, Rio Mannu di Portotorres; 3, Rio S. Miali; 4, Fiume Silis; 5, Rio Pedrasdefogu; 6, Rio Lu Bagnu; 7, Fiume Coghinas; 8, Rio S. Stefano, Caprera Island National Park; 9, Rio Cuga; 10, Rio Calvia; 11, Fiume Temo; 12, unnamed temporary rivulet near Su Peltusu Cave; 13, Rio Fraigada; 14, Fiume Tirso; 15, Rio di Siniscola; 16, Rio Berchida; 17, unnamed rivulet affluent of Rio Mannu di Milis; 18, temporary pond of Giara di Tuili; 19, Pauli Perdosu temporary pond of Giara di Gesturi; 20, Rio Mannu di Cagliari; 21, Rio Flumentepido. New records are indicated by asterisks." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615653/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). On the basis of karyological and reproductive characteristics four biotypes (A, B, C, D) have been recognized within the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M." box="[556,721,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="276 - 303" refId="ref5723" refString="Benazzi, M. (1957) Cariologia di Dugesia lugubris (O. Schmidt) (Tricladida, Paludicola). Caryologia, 10, 276 - 303. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00087114.1957.10797624" type="journal article" year="1957">Benazzi, 1957</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M. &amp; Benazzi Lentati, G." box="[733,1109,366,391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="1 - 182" refId="ref5860" refString="Benazzi, M. &amp; Benazzi Lentati, G. (1976) Platyhelminthes. In: John, B. (Ed.), Animal cytogenetics. Vol. 1. Gebruder Borntraeger, Berlin-Stuttgart, pp. 1 - 182." type="book chapter" year="1976">Benazzi &amp; Benazzi Lentati, 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,294,643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">
The first record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmidt" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[412,553,403,427]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Dugesiidae" genus="Schmidtea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tricladida" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="polychroa">
<emphasis box="[412,553,403,427]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">S. polychroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[622,715,402,427]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benazzi, M." box="[758,930,402,427]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="276 - 303" refId="ref5723" refString="Benazzi, M. (1957) Cariologia di Dugesia lugubris (O. Schmidt) (Tricladida, Paludicola). Caryologia, 10, 276 - 303. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00087114.1957.10797624" type="journal article" year="1957">Benazzi (1957)</bibRefCitation>
reported the presence of biotype A, which is amphimictic and diploid (2n = 8; n = 4). Pala and co-workers (
<bibRefCitation author="Pala, M. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Vacca, R. A." box="[869,1074,438,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="183 - 188" refId="ref7698" refString="Pala, M., Casu, S. &amp; Vacca, R. A. (1980 b) Primi dati sulla distribuzione geografica di planarie del gruppo Dugesia lugubrispolychroa (Turbellaria, Tricladida) in Sardegna, con particolare riguardo alla presenza di una mutazione tetraploide nel fiume Cixerri (Siliqua, Cagliari). Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 19, 183 - 188." type="journal article" year="1980">
Pala 
<emphasis box="[927,978,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">et al</emphasis>
., 1980b
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. &amp; Vacca, R. A." box="[1087,1283,438,463]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="177 - 184" refId="ref6163" refString="Casu, S., Pala, M. &amp; Vacca, R. A. (1982) Distribuzione geografica in Sardegna di planarie d'acqua dolce appartenenti alle specie Dugesia (S.) polychroa e Dugesia (S.) mediterranea (Turbellaria, Tricladida). Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 21, 177 - 184." type="journal article" year="1982">
Casu 
<emphasis box="[1151,1201,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">et al</emphasis>
., 1982
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacca, R. A. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M." pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="131 - 147" refId="ref9109" refString="Vacca, R. A., Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. (1988) Popolamento planariologico dei fiumi del Nord Sardegna. I. I cariotipi delle planarie d'acqua dolce del gruppo Dugesia gonocephala (Turbellaria, Tricladida) presenti nel fiume Silis (Sassari). Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 26, 131 - 147." type="journal article" year="1988">
Vacca 
<emphasis box="[1372,1422,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">et al</emphasis>
., 1988
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vacca, R. A. &amp; Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M." box="[221,278,475,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="59 - 73" refId="ref9175" refString="Vacca, R. A., Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. (1993) Popolamento planariologico dei fiumi del Nord Sardegna. II. I cariotipi dei Tricladi d'acqua dolce rinvenuti nel bacino idrografico del fiume Coghinas. Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 29, 59 - 73." type="journal article" year="1993">1993</bibRefCitation>
) highlighted the widespread distribution of biotype A and found also several populations characterized by triploid (3n = 12; n = 4) and tetraploid chromosome sets (4n = 16; n = 4), corresponding to the gynogenetic, asynaptic biotypes C and D, respectively. Biotype B was never found in 
<collectingRegion box="[954,1051,546,571]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
. Further, a new pentaploid biotype (5n = 20; n = 4) was found in a population from River Temo for which the 
<typeStatus box="[995,1043,583,607]" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">type</typeStatus>
of development is unknown (
<bibRefCitation author="Casu, S. &amp; Pala, M. &amp; Vacca, R. A." pageId="4" pageNumber="543" pagination="177 - 184" refId="ref6163" refString="Casu, S., Pala, M. &amp; Vacca, R. A. (1982) Distribuzione geografica in Sardegna di planarie d'acqua dolce appartenenti alle specie Dugesia (S.) polychroa e Dugesia (S.) mediterranea (Turbellaria, Tricladida). Bollettino della Societa Sarda di Scienze Naturali, 21, 177 - 184." type="journal article" year="1982">
Casu 
<emphasis box="[151,200,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">et al</emphasis>
., 1982
</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[301,371,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1573,1595]" captionTargetBox="[479,1117,369,1516]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[399,1187,287,1551]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Geographic distribution of species of the genus Schmidtea and Girardia recorded from Sardinia. 1, Rio Fiume Santo; 2, Rio Mannu di Portotorres; 3, Rio S. Miali; 4, Fiume Silis; 5, Rio Pedrasdefogu; 6, Rio Lu Bagnu; 7, Fiume Coghinas; 8, Rio S. Stefano, Caprera Island National Park; 9, Rio Cuga; 10, Rio Calvia; 11, Fiume Temo; 12, unnamed temporary rivulet near Su Peltusu Cave; 13, Rio Fraigada; 14, Fiume Tirso; 15, Rio di Siniscola; 16, Rio Berchida; 17, unnamed rivulet affluent of Rio Mannu di Milis; 18, temporary pond of Giara di Tuili; 19, Pauli Perdosu temporary pond of Giara di Gesturi; 20, Rio Mannu di Cagliari; 21, Rio Flumentepido. New records are indicated by asterisks." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2615653/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="543">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
